  <compounddef id="array_flipdim" kind="page">
    <compoundname>array_flipdim</compoundname>
    <title>FLIPDIM Reverse a Matrix Along a Given Dimension</title>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Section: <ref refid="sec_array_1sec_array" kindref="member">Array Generation and Manipulations</ref> </para><sect1 id="typecast_dec2bin_1USAGE">
<title>USAGE</title>
<para>Reverses an array along the given dimension. The syntax for its use is <verbatim>   y = flipdim(x,n)
</verbatim> where <computeroutput>x</computeroutput> is matrix, and <computeroutput>n</computeroutput> is the dimension to reverse. </para></sect1>
<sect1 id="variables_struct_1Example">
<title>Example</title>
<para>The following examples show some uses of <computeroutput>flipdim</computeroutput> on N-dimensional arrays.</para><para><verbatim>--&gt; x = int32(rand(4,5,3)*10)

x = 

(:,:,1) = 
  5  2  4  2  8 
  7  6  6  6  7 
  7  0  1  1  0 
  3  2  1  9  9 

(:,:,2) = 
 10  6  3  3  1 
  1  2  5  7 10 
  9  7  5  1  4 
  3 10  4  4  3 

(:,:,3) = 
  3  6  5  8  9 
  9  8  5  3  0 
  1  7  9  4  8 
  4  6  4  9  5 

--&gt; flipdim(x,1)

ans = 

(:,:,1) = 
  3  2  1  9  9 
  7  0  1  1  0 
  7  6  6  6  7 
  5  2  4  2  8 

(:,:,2) = 
  3 10  4  4  3 
  9  7  5  1  4 
  1  2  5  7 10 
 10  6  3  3  1 

(:,:,3) = 
  4  6  4  9  5 
  1  7  9  4  8 
  9  8  5  3  0 
  3  6  5  8  9 

--&gt; flipdim(x,2)

ans = 

